
=Description=

"IEEE 802.22 is '''a standard for Wireless Regional Area Network (WRAN) using white spaces in the TV frequency spectrum.''' The development of the IEEE 802.22 WRAN standard is aimed at using cognitive radio (CR) techniques to allow sharing of geographically unused spectrum allocated to the Television Broadcast Service, on a non-interfering basis, to bring broadband access to hard-to-reach, low population density areas, typical of rural environments, and is therefore timely and has the potential for a wide applicability worldwide. It is the first worldwide effort to define a standardized air interface based on CR techniques for the opportunistic use of TV television bands on a non-interfering basis."
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/802.22)


